<h1 align="center"> 
What's so great about Web Matrix?</h1> 
<p align="left"> 
&nbsp;</p> 
<blockquote>
<ul>
  <li>
  <p align="left" style="line-height: 150%; margin-bottom: 0">It is a free, 
  lightweight, easy-to-use tool for developing ASP.NET Web applications.</li>
  <li>
  <p align="left" style="line-height: 150%; margin-bottom: 0">Makes building ASP 
  applications significantly easier than other tools available</li>
  <li>
  <p align="left" style="line-height: 150%; margin-bottom: 0">If you've never 
  tried ASP.NET, then Web Matrix is a good place to start</li>
  <li>
  <p align="left" style="line-height: 150%; margin-bottom: 0">It generates HTML 
  for you<ul>
  <li>
  <p align="left" style="line-height: 150%; margin-bottom: 0">A couple of 
  drag-and-drop operations can create a simple but functional Web application</li>
  <li>
  <p align="left" style="line-height: 150%; margin-bottom: 0">You can either 
  directly edit the HTML code or make changes in the Design view</li>
</ul>
  </li>
  <li>
  <p align="left" style="line-height: 150%; margin-bottom: 0">Contains various 
  &quot;views&quot; of an ASP.NET Web page 
<ul>
  <li>
  <p align="left" style="line-height: 150%; margin-bottom: 0">both the source 
  code and HTML</li>
  <li>
  <p align="left" style="line-height: 150%; margin-bottom: 0">just the HTML 
  </li>
  <li>
  <p align="left" style="line-height: 150%; margin-bottom: 0">just the source 
  code</li>
  <li>
  <p align="left" style="line-height: 150%; margin-bottom: 0">WYSIWYG Designer<br>
  <span style="font-size: 10.0pt; font-family: Arial"><![if !supportLineBreakNewLine]>
  <br>
&nbsp;<![endif]></span></li>
</ul>
  </li>
</ul>
</blockquote>


